<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4545080>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 13. Dorsal (A), ventral (B), and lateral (C) views of the skull of Centronycteris maximiliani (AMNH 267397; male) from Paracou. Note the small anterior upper premolar and the large basisphenoid pits extending between the hamular processes of the pterygoids. C. centralis (not known from the Guianas) has a larger anterior upper premolar and smaller basisphenoid pits that do not extend between the hamular processes. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4545080/files/figure.png" .
